<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-641-710  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 641 710.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  July 1990 v27 n7 p8(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Can a single fiber carry 56 million calls?andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A single fiber-optic telephone line is capable of carrying 56million telephone calls simultaneously, according to BritishTelecom scientists.andP;  A new coherent optical system transmitted twowavelengths over fiber for 125 miles with an optical repeater 43miles from the transmitter in tests.andP;  Separation of thewavelengths can be reduced to 7 GHz before they interfere witheach other.andP;  This is more difficult in practice because the powerspectrum and the power budget are shared between many wavelengths.andO;Scientists are also working on a new transmission system thathandles more phone calls in a single channel.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   British Telecommunications PLC (research).andO;Topic:     Fiber OpticsTelephone SystemsCablesCommunications Technology.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>